    "what_description": "Helianthostylis paraensis is a species of flowering plant in the family Moraceae. It is endemic to Brazil, specifically found in the state of Par\u00e1. Helianthostylis paraensis is a climber with a woody stem, and its leaves are simple, alternate, and have a hastate shape with three lobes. The leaves are 12-20 cm long and 8-18 cm wide, with a petiole 2-4 cm long. The inflorescence is a large panicle with small male and female flowers, which are arranged in a spiral pattern.",
