    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Helianthostylis paraensis are fever, inflammation, and hypertension. Helianthostylis paraensis has been traditionally used to treat fever by inducing sweating, which helps to reduce the body temperature. Inflammation can be treated with the plant's anti-inflammatory properties, which inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes and cytokines. Hypertension has also been managed with the plant, as it contains flavonoids that have been shown to relax blood vessels and improve circulation. Additionally, the plant's antioxidant properties help to protect against oxidative stress, which can contribute to the development of various diseases, including cardiovascular disease and diabetes.",
