    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Helianthostylis paraensis are anti-inflammatory and antioxidant activities, which contribute to its ability to act as an antimicrobial agent, inhibiting the growth of various microorganisms. The anti-inflammatory property of this plant is attributed to the presence of flavonoids, saponins, and other bioactive compounds that modulate the immune response and reduce inflammation. Its antimicrobial property is also linked to the presence of these compounds, particularly flavonoids and saponins, which have been shown to exhibit bactericidal and fungicidal activities. Additionally, the antioxidant activity of Helianthostylis paraensis is responsible for its ability to scavenge free radicals, thereby protecting cells from oxidative damage and promoting cellular health. The plant's bioactive compounds, including volatile oils and other phytochemicals, also contribute to its potential as an antidiabetic agent, helping to regulate blood sugar levels and improve glucose metabolism.",
