    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Helianthostylis paraensis are flavonoids, including kaempferol and quercetin, which have been shown to exhibit anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties. Additionally, the plant contains alkaloids, such as berberine, which has been found to possess antimicrobial and anti-diabetic activities. The presence of saponins in Helianthostylis paraensis also contributes to its healing properties, as these compounds have been demonstrated to have anti-inflammatory and immunomodulatory effects. Furthermore, the plant's phenolic acids, including caffeic acid and ferulic acid, have been reported to exhibit antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities. The combination of these bioactive compounds in Helianthostylis paraensis suggests its potential use in the treatment of various health conditions, including inflammation and oxidative stress-related diseases.",
