    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Helianthostylis paraensis are infusion, tea, decoction, tincture, and salve. Infusion involves steeping the leaves of Helianthostylis paraensis in hot water to create a medicinal tea rich in flavonoids and phenolic acids. Decoction is used to extract the roots and bark, creating a liquid extract with antiseptic and anti-inflammatory properties. The tincture is made by soaking the leaves and roots in a solvent such as ethanol or glycerin to create a concentrated liquid extract with antioxidant and antimicrobial activities. A salve is prepared by infusing the leaves in a carrier oil, creating a topical application for skin conditions and wounds due to its antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory effects.",
